  "texts": [
    "A high correlation (r = 0.79) of the social anxiety predicted by GPT-4 with the actual self-report social anxiety score on the SPIN questionnaire proves the potential of this approach.",
    "However, our findings should be considered as a starting point for further research into the performance of different LLMs with different amounts of pre-training and the potential for an automated interview.",
    "A limitation lies with the ground truth in this study being a self-report measure and not a valid diagnosis of social anxiety disorder (SAD).",
    "An investigation comparing LLM results to actual clinical diagnoses constitutes a necessary next step.",
    "Scientific Reports | (2024) 14:30498 2 | https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-024-82192-2"
  ],
